CHANNELS: Communication lines for staff and players

AetherMUD has no player-facing chat channels. All player-to-player
communication is room-local (the same reach as say), with two
exceptions: the radio system and psionic telepathy, both below.
There is no global OOC channel, no newbie/guild/gossip lines, and no
channel toggles, because there is no channel to toggle.

ROOM-LOCAL (everyone in your current room)
  say <message>          speak, subject to the language system
  ooc <message>          speak out-of-character, skips language checks
  shout <message>        speak loudly, skips language checks,
                          5-second cooldown
  whisper <who> <msg>    private, only the named player hears it
  emote <action>         perform an action

CROSS-ROOM (the only two ways to reach someone not in your room)
  radio <message>        broadcast on your radio's tuned frequency;
                          only other radios on the same frequency
                          hear it (see: radio)
  telepathy <who> <msg>  psionic power; requires the telepathy
                          psionic, ISP, and a prior introduction to
                          the target (see: introduce)

STAFF CONTACT
  tell <staff> <msg>     contact online wizard staff; mortals cannot
                          tell other mortals this way
  reply <msg>            reply to the last tell you received

WIZARD STAFF ONLY (genuinely restricted, not channels mortals are
missing out on)
  wiz <message>           broadcasts to every online wizard,
                          regardless of room
  yell <message>          the command exists but reports "does not
                          exist" to non-staff

SEE ALSO: communication, radio, telepathy, introduce, tell
